                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                        </seg>
                        <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                        <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#114v"/> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#124r #124v"/> (tenth Biblical Canticle).</desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>
                        <desc> print card of <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/> is pasted onto the folio. With caption <q>“David, King of Israel with his harp,” in Amharic</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#iir(ecto)"/>
                        <desc> print card of <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/> is pasted onto the folio. Caption in Amharic and Gə‘əz: <q>“With her beloved Son, protector of the Ethiopian people, and Redeemer of the World.”</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#iiv(erso)"/>
                        <desc> print card of King <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/> is pasted onto the folio. Caption in Gə‘əz: <q>“King David.”</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#iiir(ecto)"/>
                        <desc> print card of <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/> is pasted onto the folio. Captions in Cyrillic</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#ivv(erso)"/>
                        <desc> print card of Sacred Heart of <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1099StMary"/> is pasted onto the folio. Caption in French: <q>“N. D. des 3 AVE MARIA. Par votre Puissance, votre Sagesse, votre Misericorde, O Marie Immaculée <gap reason="omitted"/> [illegible].”</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6">
                        <locus target="#21v"/>
                        <desc> a bird, in pencil</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7">
                        <locus target="#135r"/>
                        <desc> a print card of “When Paul Met <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1084JesusChrist"/>" is pasted onto the folio. Caption is in English: <q>“When Paul Met Jesus. Lesson Material—Acts 9:1–31.  Memory Verse—I am not ashamed of the gospel.” Romans 1:16.”</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8">
                        <locus target="#135v"/>
                        <desc> a print card of <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1039Magi"/> Note at the bottom: “©Providence Lithograph Co. The World Council of Christian Education NT–A–2.”.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d9">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #22r #64r #128r #136r #144r"/> (haräg);
                    lines of alternating red and black dots are used as section dividers throughout
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#iiiv(erso) #ivr(ecto)"/>": Layman’s prayer, in Amharic, <foreign xml:lang="am">አዳምን፡ ከሲኦል፡ ኖኅን፡ ከማየ፡ አይኅ፡</foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#148r #148v #149r #149v"/> 
                              <title type="complete" ref="LIT3108RepCh388"/> in a different hand
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#ir(ecto) #115v"/>: blank
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 33
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    blue yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#1 #44 #101 #136"/>;
                    yellow yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#22 #72 #116"/>;
                    black yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#31 #77"/>;
                    green yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#39 #64 #89 #109"/>;
                    purple yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#53 #103 #128"/>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–9 and 12
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>
                    Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#38v #39r #40v #49v"/>);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#36r"/>);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#29v #35v #37v #55v #81v"/>, etc.).
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
